text:
this problem occur if there is an include file in a html which is more that 8k.
version 3.1 and below did not have this problem. only this problem
occured  on 3.2.**

I have trace until i found out that   class   
org/apache/tomcat/core/BufferServletOutputStream.java
have modified   from 3.1 to 3.2

function below didnot have a statement to reset the commit status

    public void recycle() {
	// 	System.out.println("Recycle BOS " );
	bufferCount = 0;
	totalCount = 0;
	closed = false;
    usingWriter = false;
    }

the correct one i assumed ,since it is working.

    public void recycle() {
	// 	System.out.println("Recycle BOS " );
	bufferCount = 0;
	totalCount = 0;
	closed = false;
    usingWriter = false;
  // statement to reset commit status
    resA.setBufferCommitted(false);
    }
